I consider including a mocking library instead of manual fakes? Also, I'll need to check the documentation for building a WebDAV server or client, as I don't want any dependencies on external servers.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying setup guidance**\\n\\nI need to remember not to restate deterministic entries in my guidance, so I’ll avoid mentioning the servlet dependency. The instructions say that no Docker image or environment/system properties are needed. I should cover client method/request XML builders and server abstractions using in-memory XML and simple fakes to avoid a live HTTP/WebDAV server. Is it acceptable to include \\\"No Docker\\\" as a non-deterministic entry? The agent guidance should focus on environmental properties or test setup, but leaving it as an empty string might be an option too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Jackrabbit WebDAV exposes servlet-based server APIs, and its POM marks the servlet API as provided, so generated tests need an explicit test dependency to compile and exercise meaningful servlet-facing coverage.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The artifact contains WebDAV request/response, input/output context, and AbstractWebdavServlet classes whose public APIs reference javax.servlet and javax.servlet.http types; the Maven artifact declares servlet-api as provided, so it is not supplied transitively to tests.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or environment/system property setup is indicated. Prefer in-memory tests for XML/property/method classes and simple fake servlet request/response objects rather than relying on a live WebDAV server.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The library was compiled against an old provided servlet API; use javax.servlet-era APIs, not jakarta.servlet.\",\n    \"Some native-image failures may still be metadata/reflection issues unrelated to setup; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03856c72bb122212016a42724987ec819397d5ed60e6a13609\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1157, "output": 782, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35731, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782739518328, "responseId": "resp_03856c72bb122212016a42723ec99081939dab261e68a246d5"}, "toolResults": []}
